"After the recent RSA conference in London, RSA's top management gave some indications of the company's vision for the future, together with its strategies, both technological and financial. The objective is to become a billion dollar per-year company (which it originally planned to do by this year), while shifting from the ‘simple’ provision of technology and services to more advanced activities that will include high-level consulting. We interviewed two of the most representative RSA executives – Chris Young, vice-president of products, and Tom Heiser, worldwide operations – to get their view of things."
